am\": \"a dictatorship\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"a functioning, healthy democracy\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are, in fact, some undeniable similarities between the actions of fictional Dictator Aladeen in the 2012 movie and those of India's current rulers on the eve of the 2024 election.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9999997762688758, \"rank\": 2.0253208686723336e-07, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \", some undeniable similarities\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"the actions\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"fictional Dictator Aladeen\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2012 movie\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1596}, {\"ngram\": \"the eve\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 election\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1664}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prime Minister Narendra Modi's ruling Bharatiya Janata Party, for example, launched its large-scale, state-funded election campaign long before the date for the election was announced and campaigning budgets for all parties were allocated.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1682, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Narendra Modi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\"}, {\"begin\": 1705, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bharatiya_Janata_Party\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.2569910476507055e-12, \"text\": \"Bharatiya Janata Party\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bharatiya_Janata_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bharatiya_Janata_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1740}, {\"ngram\": \"its large-scale, state-funded election campaign\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1798}, {\"ngram\": \"the date\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1819}, {\"ngram\": \"the election\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1836}, {\"ngram\": \"budgets\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1874}, {\"ngram\": \"all parties\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1890}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thus, it had a head start over the opposition political parties.\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1971, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a head\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1926}, {\"ngram\": \"the opposition political parties\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1970}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore, just before the announcement of the dates for the 2024 elections, the government amended the rules for selecting members of the Election Commission overseeing the vote.\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2114, \"end\": 2133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Election_Commission_of_India\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.401261587964783e-33, \"text\": \"Election Commission\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Election_Commission_of_India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Election_Commission_of_India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the announcement\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2014}, {\"ngram\": \"the dates\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2027}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 elections\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2066}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"members\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2106}, {\"ngram\": \"the vote\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier, the selection committee included the prime minister and the leader of the opposition as well as the chief justice of India.\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2281, \"end\": 2286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9999997762688758, \"rank\": 2.0253208686723336e-07, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the selection committee\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"the prime minister\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2215}, {\"ngram\": \"the leader\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"the opposition\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2248}, {\"ngram\": \"the chief justice\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2277}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was to ensure some impartiality in the selection.\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2342, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some impartiality\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"the selection\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this year, the government abruptly changed the rules.\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2400, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2372}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It removed the chief justice from the committee and replaced him with a government minister to be appointed by the PM.\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2519, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the chief justice\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"the committee\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2448}, {\"ngram\": \"a government minister\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2492}, {\"ngram\": \"the PM\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2518}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This means that now the government's opinion will be paramount in the selection of the Election Commission.\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2607, \"end\": 2626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Election_Commission_of_India\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.401261587964783e-33, \"text\": \"Election Commission\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Election_Commission_of_India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Election_Commission_of_India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the government's opinion\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2564}, {\"ngram\": \"the selection\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2599}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is as if the captain of only one of the several teams participating in a game appoints the umpire.\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2729, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the captain\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2651}, {\"ngram\": \"the several teams\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2684}, {\"ngram\": \"a game\", \"from\": 2702, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"the umpire\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2728}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What is then left to say about the impartiality of the Election Commission?\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2785, \"end\": 2804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Election_Commission_of_India\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.401261587964783e-33, \"text\": \"Election Commission\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Election_Commission_of_India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Election_Commission_of_India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the impartiality\", \"from\": 2761, \"to\": 2777}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just after the announcement of elections, on March 21, Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal, the leader of the opposition Aam Aadmi Party, was arrested by India's financial crime agency, the Enforcement Directorate (ED) which alleged that he was the mastermind of a scam relating to Delhi's new liquor excise policy.\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 3123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2862, \"end\": 2867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Delhi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.108989446063058e-15, \"text\": \"Delhi\", \"types\": [\"Q486972